Commentary Text: Shami to Karthik, out Caught by Rahul!! DK has been given OUT caught behind and he has reviewed it straightaway. It's a fair delivery, there's a definite sound, don't think the bat hit the pad either. UltraEdge in and there's a spike when the ball went past the bat. 'Clear spike', says the third umpire and Karthik has to go. KKR in a real soup now. DK hasn't just gone for a duck, but he has taken away the only review available for his team as well. It's 10 for 3 and KKR are rocking here badly. Superb delivery from Shami, pitched up in that channel outside off and that late seam movement does another batsman in - DK was striding forward on the defensive push, the ball found the edge and KL did the rest. Karthik c Rahul b Shami 0(2)

Commentary Text: Chakravarthy to Rahul, out Lbw!! My, my, my! First the national call up and now the wicket of the Orange Cap holder. It's getting better for Varun Chakravarthy. This was the quicker delivery that spun back, beat Rahul on the flick, beaten for pace, impact in line with middle and leg, but with the ball turning there was a bit of doubt, umpire Richard Illingworth though thought and raised the finger. Wonder what Mandeep told Rahul when they discussed the review. Surely he had to review that with the doubt and they could have retained the review if it was umpire's call. KXIP would be hoping now that it's not missing leg. Rahul's not-so-great-time against spin continues. Rahul lbw b Chakravarthy 28(25) [4s-4]
